From 37137183ee37f9fe4ba36ad363cbd9fd91265928 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dfattal <dfattal@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 23:29:35 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 06/39] B3: WebXR inline-3D JS surface + head-tracked 2-view
 off-axis session + teardown (#625)

Checkpoint of the full B3 slice on the displayxr-inline-3d patch branch (mirrors
the B2a/B2b/B2c checkpoints). content_shell builds + links clean; feature-detection
verified both polarities on Leia. Per-element weave + 2-view eyeball deferred to B4
(content_shell page-flatten stops the per-element tag reaching Viz).

B3a  per-element weave_target tag: cc::TextureLayer -> TextureLayerImpl ->
     TextureDrawQuad -> quads.mojom (getter+Read) -> SkiaRenderer::DrawTextureQuad;
     DisplayXRInline3D RuntimeEnabledFeature; tag carried pending->active.
B3b  navigator.xr.requestSession('inline-3d') (Blink-local sensorless inline) +
     XRDisplayLayer (ScriptWrappable) tagging the target canvas via
     HTMLCanvasElement::SetInline3D.
B3c  per-element committed rect (ExternalUseClient::ImageContext::weave_rect);
     MaybeWeaveSubstitute loops all tagged contexts, per-target state keyed by
     source canvas mailbox.
B3d  two head-tracked eye views: is_inline_3d threaded through session creation;
     UpdateInlineView builds 2 XRViewData with window-relative off-axis (Kooima)
     projections (UpdateProjectionMatrixFromFoV) + per-eye poses (SetMojoFromView);
     new blink-accessible DisplayXRService mojom (IsInline3DSupported, GetLatestEyes)
     bound frame-scoped in content/shell; browser caches eyes + committed rect and
     queries XR_EXT_display_info for the display geometry.
B3e  isSessionSupported('inline-3d') routes through DisplayXRService (async, with a
     disconnect-driven negative control); XRSession tracks + closes its
     XRDisplayLayers on session end (untag); GPU displayxr_weave_state_ pruned each
     frame for source mailboxes no longer tagged.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
